Property.Name: empAgreementIntro
Property.sap:label: I agree that my employment is subject to the following: My agreement to undertake a pre-employment functional skills and aptitude assessment as requested by JBS at any time during the pre-employment process and at any time during my employment with JBS. Agree that as part of this pre-employment application and at any time during my employment I consent to provide specimens for medical, drug and alcohol tests to ensure my safety and the safety of others. To abide by JBS policies and procedures and to make myself aware of circumstances applicable to my employment. To adhere to security procedures. To work a reasonable amount of overtime to meet the needs of the business, shift work (including night work) public holidays and to participate in designated training as required by JBS. To work within all terms and conditions of the relevant site industrial agreement. To accept changes in my role, tasks, duties and responsibilities as required by JBS. To adopt safe work practices for myself and my co-workers. To agree to be paid by bank deposit, weekly, fortnightly or monthly at JBS discretion. To agree to show the contents of my locker, bag and or vehicle if requested by an authorised person of JBS whilst on JBS premises. To return all JBS property prior to leaving or terminating from JBS and if unable to do so agree to have an amount equal to the value of the missing property deducted from my final pay. I have read and understand, or have had read to me and understand, all the details on this application form. I declare that the information provided by me in this application form, and on my resume, is true and correct, and that I am responsible for the accuracy of the information given by me. If any of the information I have provided is found by JBS to have been withheld, suppressed, or to be misleading or false, I understand that I am liable to be dismissed from employment if this application for employment is successful.

Property.Name: hearing1Intro
Property.sap:label: As an applicant for employment with JBS Australia, I have been advised: That the Company has in place a Workplace Health and Safety programme. As part of that programme and because of the provisions of the Workers Compensation Legislation (relating to hearing loss), all employees (other than administrative) prior to commencing employment, must take a hearing test. I agree that if my hearing test discloses any hearing loss, I will complete a Notice of Claim form. I authorise JBS prior to my commencing work, to give to my previous employer Notice of Claim for my hearing loss, on the appropriate form. I authorise JBS to complete the form with the percentage of losses disclosed by tests.

Property.Name: medical1Intro
Property.sap:label: To ensure JBS Australia meets its workplace health and safety obligations we require all job applicants to undergo a medical examination as part of your application for employment. This examination may include testing for illegal drugs or other substances. Please note that if you are employed by JBS Australia it will be a condition of your employment that you undergo further medical examinations and tests, including for illegal drugs or alcohol, at the direction and discretion of JBS Australia. JBS Australia does not discriminate against its employees or prospective employees; it does however have an obligation to ensure that its workers can safely perform the inherent requirements of the role for which they are employed. If you are a suitable candidate for employment with JBS Australia and you have a pre-existing medical condition, further questions will be asked in relation to that condition to ascertain that you can perform the inherent requirements of the role or what reasonable adjustments to the role may be necessary to assist you to perform its inherent requirements.

Property.Name: zoonotic1Intro
Property.sap:label: The company takes this opportunity to inform you that there are diseases that can be contracted from animals slaughtered in abattoirs. These diseases are commonly called Zoonotic diseases. Infection from these diseases can be minimised by following simple hygiene procedures, which will be fully explained to you should your application for employment be successful. In addition, a compulsory vaccination programme is in place to minimise the risk of contracting Q fever (a zoonotic disease). If you are unable to be vaccinated and are not already immune to Q-fever, you will not be eligible for employment at any of JBS mainland Australia meat processing facilities or feedlots, in accordance with our No Jab, No Job policy. While all possible care is taken to ensure you are immune to Q fever, the process is not 100% secure. During the screening process, a very small number of persons, where either the blood test or skin test show a positive reaction that suggests immunity may be showing a false positive, or it may indicate a 'cellular' immunity but not immunity to infection. In those vaccinated, there is a small possibility that the vaccine may not result in the development of immunity or there may be a failure of the vaccine." Should you have any concerns about the nature of zoonotic diseases and/or the risks of contracting such diseases, please consult your Doctor.

Property.Name: empAgreementIntro
Property.sap:label: I agree that my employment is subject to the following: My agreement to undertake a pre-employment functional skills and aptitude assessment as requested by JBS at any time during the pre-employment process and at any time during my employment with JBS. Agree that as part of this pre-employment application and at any time during my employment I consent to provide specimens for medical, drug and alcohol tests to ensure my safety and the safety of others. To abide by JBS policies and procedures and to make myself aware of circumstances applicable to my employment. To adhere to security procedures. To work a reasonable amount of overtime to meet the needs of the business, shift work (including night work) public holidays and to participate in designated training as required by JBS. To work within all terms and conditions of the relevant site industrial agreement. To accept changes in my role, tasks, duties and responsibilities as required by JBS. To adopt safe work practices for myself and my co-workers. To agree to be paid by bank deposit, weekly, fortnightly or monthly at JBS discretion. To agree to show the contents of my locker, bag and or vehicle if requested by an authorised person of JBS whilst on JBS premises. To return all JBS property prior to leaving or terminating from JBS and if unable to do so agree to have an amount equal to the value of the missing property deducted from my final pay. I have read and understand, or have had read to me and understand, all the details on this application form. I declare that the information provided by me in this application form, and on my resume, is true and correct, and that I am responsible for the accuracy of the information given by me. If any of the information I have provided is found by JBS to have been withheld, suppressed, or to be misleading or false, I understand that I am liable to be dismissed from employment if this application for employment is successful.

Property.Name: hearing1Intro
Property.sap:label: As an applicant for employment with JBS Australia, I have been advised: That the Company has in place a Workplace Health and Safety programme. As part of that programme and because of the provisions of the Workers Compensation Legislation (relating to hearing loss), all employees (other than administrative) prior to commencing employment, must take a hearing test. I agree that if my hearing test discloses any hearing loss, I will complete a Notice of Claim form. I authorise JBS prior to my commencing work, to give to my previous employer Notice of Claim for my hearing loss, on the appropriate form. I authorise JBS to complete the form with the percentage of losses disclosed by tests.

Property.Name: medical1Intro
Property.sap:label: To ensure JBS Australia meets its workplace health and safety obligations we require all job applicants to undergo a medical examination as part of your application for employment. This examination may include testing for illegal drugs or other substances. Please note that if you are employed by JBS Australia it will be a condition of your employment that you undergo further medical examinations and tests, including for illegal drugs or alcohol, at the direction and discretion of JBS Australia. JBS Australia does not discriminate against its employees or prospective employees; it does however have an obligation to ensure that its workers can safely perform the inherent requirements of the role for which they are employed. If you are a suitable candidate for employment with JBS Australia and you have a pre-existing medical condition, further questions will be asked in relation to that condition to ascertain that you can perform the inherent requirements of the role or what reasonable adjustments to the role may be necessary to assist you to perform its inherent requirements.

Property.Name: zoonotic1Intro
Property.sap:label: The company takes this opportunity to inform you that there are diseases that can be contracted from animals slaughtered in abattoirs. These diseases are commonly called Zoonotic diseases. Infection from these diseases can be minimised by following simple hygiene procedures, which will be fully explained to you should your application for employment be successful. In addition, a compulsory vaccination programme is in place to minimise the risk of contracting Q fever (a zoonotic disease). If you are unable to be vaccinated and are not already immune to Q-fever, you will not be eligible for employment at any of JBS mainland Australia meat processing facilities or feedlots, in accordance with our No Jab, No Job policy. While all possible care is taken to ensure you are immune to Q fever, the process is not 100% secure. During the screening process, a very small number of persons, where either the blood test or skin test show a positive reaction that suggests immunity may be showing a false positive, or it may indicate a 'cellular' immunity but not immunity to infection. In those vaccinated, there is a small possibility that the vaccine may not result in the development of immunity or there may be a failure of the vaccine." Should you have any concerns about the nature of zoonotic diseases and/or the risks of contracting such diseases, please consult your Doctor.
